{
  "text": "For such problems, it is thus a requirement for the solution to satisfy y 0, a condition which is fulfilled with non-negative Dirichlet boundary conditions. We might consider using controls that are above 1, taking into account the possibility for releases at 0 or L to be above the capacity of the system. However, there are contexts in which y is the proportion of individuals of type A over the total number of individuals of types A and B. This can be obtained as the suitable limit of a system of two reaction-diffusion equations for each type [CITATION_1] . Thus, we shall also impose that the controls are below 1 to cover these cases, which will not be a restriction for the results.",
